This paper deals with the analysis of the expected number of maximal points in a set of points chosen from a distribution, which is a problem in computational geometry and data structures (cs.CG and cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of the effect of random noise on the input distribution, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The analysis involves probabilistic techniques and the study of functions of multiple variables, which are topics in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the applications of maximal points in various settings, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
